Israeli Doctors to Strike for Hospital Wage Hike, Haaretz Says

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   F e r z i g e r
-- 
2011-04-04T05:24:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/israeli-doctors-to-strike-for-hospital-wage-hike-haaretz-says.html
Israeli doctors have declared a
strike that is planned to start tomorrow, demanding a 50 percent
increase in hourly wages at hospitals and health clinics,
Haaretz said, citing the Israeli Medical Association. The last
doctors strike took place in 2000 and lasted more than four
months, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
